title: If the display property of an item is set to 'none', it doesn't take effect in new PDF emitter.
OB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, the item is still visible in the generated PDF.
EB: Expected behavior: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, the item should be invisible in the generated PDF.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Open the new PDF emitter. 
2. Set the display property of an item to 'none'. 
3. Generate a PDF. 
4. Check if the item is still visible in the generated PDF.
